 System Architecture Specification: Enterprise Ordering & Live Synchronization Platform
This document serves as the absolute technical reference for the production-grade, zero-licensing-cost, multi-tenant-ready restaurant ordering and real-time kitchen execution platform.

1. System Topology & Network Infrastructure
The system employs a high-concurrency, decoupled architecture. All client traffic is ingested via an edge reverse proxy that segregates stateful (WebSocket) connections from stateless (REST) traffic. The application compute layer is entirely stateless, offloading volatile state to an in-memory Redis cluster and transactional state to a highly optimized PostgreSQL instance.

