5. Failure Modes, Edge Cases, & Resilience Architecture
To keep the platform highly reliable without relying on expensive infrastructure, the codebase must handle unexpected failures natively.

5.1 Connection Interruption & State Reconciliation Strategy
The Issue: A user locks their mobile device or drives through a cellular dead zone after submitting an order. The WebSocket connection drops, causing them to miss the ORDER_PAID or ORDER_READY event.

The Mitigation Protocol: 1.  The client UI must never rely exclusively on real-time event notifications for absolute truth.
2.  Upon reconnecting to the network, the Flutter app must instantly fire an optimized HTTP GET request to /api/v1/orders/active to reconcile its local state with PostgreSQL.
3.  The client implementation must implement Exponential Backoff Reconnection logic. If a connection drops, it retries after 1 second, then 2 seconds, 4 seconds, and 8 seconds, capping at 16 seconds to avoid overwhelming the server.

5.2 Network State Engine Logic (Flutter Client-Side)
Dart
import 'dart:async';
import 'dart:convert';
import 'package:web_socket_channel/io.dart';

class RealTimeSyncService {
  IOWebSocketChannel? _channel;
  Timer? _heartbeatTimer;
  bool _isConnecting = false;
  int _retrySeconds = 1;
  final String _connectionUrl;

  RealTimeSyncService(this._connectionUrl);

  void establishConnection() {
    if (_isConnecting) return;
    _isConnecting = true;

    try {
      _channel = IOWebSocketChannel.connect(Uri.parse(_connectionUrl));
      _retrySeconds = 1; // Reset backoff timer on successful connection
      _isConnecting = false;

      // Start the heartbeat loop to prevent connection dropouts
      _initiateHeartbeatLoop();

      _channel!.stream.listen(
        (message) {
          _processIncomingPayload(message);
        },
        onDone: () => _handleConnectionFailure(),
        onError: (error) => _handleConnectionFailure(),
        cancelOnError: true,
      );
    } catch (e) {
      _isConnecting = false;
      _handleConnectionFailure();
    }
  }

  void _initiateHeartbeatLoop() {
    _heartbeatTimer?.cancel();
    _heartbeatTimer = Timer.periodic(Duration(seconds: 30), (timer) {
      if (_channel != null) {
        _channel!.sink.add(jsonEncode({"type": "ping"}));
      }
    });
  }

  void _handleConnectionFailure() {
    _heartbeatTimer?.cancel();
    _channel?.sink.close();
    
    // Execute structural exponential backoff retry logic
    Timer(Duration(seconds: _retrySeconds), () {
      _retrySeconds = (_retrySeconds * 2).clamp(1, 16);
      establishConnection();
    });
  }

  void _processIncomingPayload(String message) {
    final Map<String, dynamic> payload = jsonDecode(message);
    if (payload['type'] == 'pong') return; // Handshake acknowledgment
    
    // Route state updates directly to UI managers (e.g., Riverpod/Provider notification blocks)
  }
