5.3 Database Connection Pool Exhaustion Protection
The Issue: High concurrent menu access exhausts PostgreSQL connection parameters, causing requests to time out.

The Mitigation Protocol: 1.  Read Optimization: The menu catalog must never be read directly from PostgreSQL on every request. On application startup, the entire menu catalog is compiled into a JSON string and stored in Redis with an absolute key reference (menu:store_id).
2.  When a user requests the menu, FastAPI serves it directly from Redis memory in under 10 milliseconds, completely bypassing PostgreSQL.
3.  When the store owner modifies an item on the admin dashboard, the update endpoint executes a database write followed by an instant cache invalidation call (redis.del("menu:store_id")), forcing an on-demand update on the next request.

